# HEARTBEAT.md

## Purpose
This file defines the main agent heartbeat. You are not tied to any project.

## Required inputs
- Credentials (BASE_URL, AUTH_TOKEN, AGENT_ID): read from `{{ credential_path }}`.
- API guidance: `skills/mission-control/SKILL.md` — the single source of truth for every
  API call. Read it; do not improvise commands.

If the credential file or skill is missing, stop and request a provisioning update.

## How to call the API
Follow `skills/mission-control/SKILL.md`: read the credential file, then run `curl` with
the values written straight into the command. Do not build shell variables or use
`$(...)`. Endpoints for your role are listed in `skills/mission-control/references/api_schema.md`.

## Schedule
- If a heartbeat schedule is configured, send a lightweight check-in only.
- On first cycle after wake/bootstrap, run heartbeat check-in immediately (do not wait for cadence).
- Do not claim or move project tasks unless explicitly instructed by Mission Control.
- If you have any pending `LEAD REQUEST: ASK USER` messages in OpenClaw chat, handle them promptly (see AGENTS.md).

## Heartbeat checklist
1) Check in immediately using the heartbeat call from the skill
   (`POST /api/v1/agent/heartbeat`).
2) If check-in fails due to 5xx/network, stop and retry next heartbeat. During that
   failure window, do **not** write memory updates (`MEMORY.md`, daily memory files).

## Memory Maintenance (every 2-3 days)
1) Read recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files.
2) Update `MEMORY.md` with durable facts/decisions and evolving preferences/identity.
3) Prune stale content.

## Common mistakes (avoid)
- Claiming project tasks without instruction.
- Improvising API commands instead of following the skill.

## When to say HEARTBEAT_OK
You may say `HEARTBEAT_OK` only when:
1) Heartbeat check-in succeeded, and
2) Any pending high-priority gateway-main duty for this cycle was handled (if present), and
3) No outage rule was violated (no memory writes during 5xx/network failure window).

Do **not** say `HEARTBEAT_OK` if check-in failed.
